 As expected, if the video was only shown to the female co-head, significantly
 less men were able to answer correctly: the percentage of correct responses
 decreases by 14.3 percentage points.
 In other words, if men did not get the information, only about 12 percent
 of men knew the answer.
 This is virtually the same as the proportion of female co-heads that answered
 the question correctly without having seen the video (12.6) percent.
 Also according to expectations, showing the video to the female co-head
